title: Encephalocele: Epidemiology and Demographics
short_description: CDC statistics on encephalocele birth prevalence, showing approximately 375 cases annually in the US with gender and geographic variations in location.
long_description: This document presents epidemiological data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention regarding encephalocele, a neural tube defect. It details the annual incidence rate of approximately 1 in 10,000 births (375 cases per year) in the United States, highlighting important demographic patterns including gender-based differences in anatomical location and geographic variations in presentation between Western populations and Southeast Asian populations.
